      <p>Acrylics — Crafted premium plexiglass showcasing vivid and modern design.</p>
      <p>Metals — Sleek and modern aluminum products that are fade and scratch resistant.</p>
      <p>Albums — Personalized photobooks to luxurious Heirloom albums.</p>
      <p>Grad Gear — Announcements, invites, banners and thank you cards.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <dl class="seo-faq">
        <dt>How far in advance should I book?</dt>
        <dd>For senior portraits, 3–6 months ahead is ideal. Family sessions usually book 1–3 months out. Mini sessions sell out within days of advertising due to limited spots.</dd>
        <dt>How many outfit changes can I bring?</dt>
        <dd>Seniors should bring up to 3 outfit changes. For families, one coordinated look usually works. You will receive a detailed style guide once you have booked.</dd>
        <dt>What happens if it rains?</dt>
        <dd>I'll text you 24 hours before and we'll reschedule — no extra charge. A little overcast? That's perfect for photos.</dd>
        <dt>Where do sessions take place?</dt>
        <dd>On location throughout Southeast Michigan. I've shot at dozens of locations in Livingston County, Oakland County, and beyond.</dd>
        <dt>When will I receive my photos?</dt>
        <dd>Within 2–3 weeks you'll receive a link to your private gallery along with a print release.</dd>
      </dl>
    </section>

